                              red dividing line

                   Contacting the New York State Archives

                 Phone numbers and electronic mail addresses
                      for contacting the State Archives

   red dividing line


  For questions about the records in the State Archives, hours of the research
  room, etc:

     * Via Electronic Mail: Reference Services
     * Via Telephone: (518) 474-8955

  Records Management assistance for State Agencies:

     * Via Electronic Mail: Records Management Services
     * Via Telephone: (518) 474-6926

  Records Management grants and assistance for Local Governments:

     * Contact your Regional Advisory Officer
     * State Archives Albany Office Via Telephone: (518) 474-6926

  Documentary Heritage Program of grants and assistance for non-government
  historical records repositories:

     * Contact your DHP Regional Archivist
     * Contact the DHP office in Albany(dhs@mail.nysed.gov)
     * Contact the DHP Office in Albany Via Telephone:(518) 474-6926

  For comments or questions about the Rediscovering New York History & Culture
  Web Site:

     * Via electronic mail: dhs@mail.nysed.gov
     * Via Telephone: (518) 474-6926

  For comments or questions about documentation projects of the New York State
  Archives including environmental, mental health, and Latino/a projects:

     * Via electronic mail: dhs@mail.nysed.gov
     * Via telephone: (518) 474-6926

  Other questions?

     * Via Telephone at: (518) 474-6926
     * Via E-Mail at: sarainfo@mail.nysed.gov
     * By postal mail at:
        New York State Archives and Records Administration
            New York State Education Department
            Cultural Education Center
            Albany, NY 12230
